<h2>Estate Planning for Monroeville Families</h2>

<p>We create customized estate plans for Monroeville residents that include wills, powers of attorney under 20 Pa.C.S. § 5601, healthcare directives, and revocable living trusts when they serve the client's goals. Monroeville's many professional families — physicians at Forbes Regional Hospital, executives in the business park corridor, and entrepreneurs throughout the municipality — often have complex planning needs that include coordination of multiple retirement accounts, employer-provided benefits, business interests, and real estate holdings. We ensure every piece of the puzzle fits together.</p>

<h2>Probate and Estate Administration</h2>

<p>Monroeville estates are generally administered through the Allegheny County Register of Wills at the City-County Building in downtown Pittsburgh. We guide Monroeville executors and administrators through every stage — will filing, Short Certificate issuance, creditor notification, asset inventory, PA Inheritance Tax Return preparation (REV-1500), and final distribution. For estates with property in Westmoreland County as well, we handle the ancillary filings and coordinate across both jurisdictions to minimize delays and complications.</p>

<h2>Real Estate Closings</h2>

<p>Monroeville's active residential market — from homes in Garden City and Tall Trees to newer construction throughout the municipality — benefits from our full settlement services. As licensed title insurance agents through Chicago Title and First American, we handle title searches, issue title insurance policies, prepare closing documents, and attend settlement. We record deeds with the Allegheny County Department of Real Estate and coordinate with lenders and agents to keep every transaction on schedule.</p>

